"display ..." statements can be commands or program lines.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

display 0        simulation-run display OFF
display 1        simulation-run display ON (default)
display 2        don't erase display between runs (no command mode)

display A        produces xy-coordinate system for interpreter plot
display B        produces xt-coordinate system for interpreter plot

display Cn, display C n    sets color n for coordinate net;
                            n=16 black (no coordinate net);
                            n=17 white background

display Nn, display N n    sets color n for first curve;
                            n=15 all curves are white;
                            n=16 all curves are black

display F        erases all screens


display Q        produces thin dots/lines (default)
display R        produces thick dots/lines
display S        turns graphics OFF after interpreter plots

display W x,y	sets display-window origin

